                            BATTLEZONE:
                     A game for ST and Falcon by:
                          Andrew & Ian Gower

xoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxo


     We all remember  Lemmings  (and  so  did  the  programmer of this
game;) but BattleZone owes more to another  game of a similar name in
which you control a tank and attempt to  destroy your opponent (also a
tank) by firing shells across  the  screen  and judging both the angle
and amount of power needed to  achieve  a direct hit.  Battlezone, '96
style, requires these same skills but in  a form similar to  the Amiga
game Worms...  so with all  these  precedents  you  should have a good
idea of just which genre to file this game under (and please don't say
'miscellaneous unlabelled disk pile' or I'll start to s c
